Nigeria on Thursday recorded 167 total deaths from coronavirus (COVID-19) According to the data from the Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, three deaths were recorded on Thursday. On Wednesday, the country had a total of 164 deaths. While on Tuesday, the total number of deaths was 158 a difference of eight deaths from Mondayâ€™s tally at 150. This brings the total of confirmed deaths from complication of Coronavirus to seventeen(17) between Tuesday and Thursday night. According to NCDC data, there is a decrease in number of deaths recorded in Nigeria compared to Sunday, 11th May. DAILY POST recalls that Nigeria on Sunday recorded fifteen COVID-19 related deaths in a single day. Meanwhile, Nigeria has passed the 5,000 mark with a total of 5162 COVID-19 cases, and 1180 recoveries.